<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>10 SPEED TRANSMISSIONS EATON RTLO SERIES - REMOVE - REAR AUXILIARY DRIVE GEAR</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="remove" graphiccount="2">
        <title>REAR AUXILIARY DRIVE GEAR</title>
        <para>Due to a design change, some models may have a round retainer that holds the rear auxiliary drive gear in
            position. Along with the round retainer, there will be two (2) thrust washers: one (1) behind the retainer
            and one (1) behind the rear auxiliary driver gear.
        </para>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">On the output shaft, temporarily install a output yoke (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1301759">Figure 59</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1301759" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1301759" filename="../figg13/G1301759.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 59. Temporary Output Yoke</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">To keep the output shaft from turning, insert a breaker bar (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1301759">Figure 59</hotlnk>).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the 15/16" bolt and retainer from the output shaft. If the retainer is round, there
                will also be a thrust washer behind the retainer to remove. Remove the bar and output yoke (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1301760">Figure 60</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1301760" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1301760" filename="../figg13/G1301760.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 60. Remove Auxiliary Drive Gear</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the auxiliary drive gear from the output shaft (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1301760">Figure 60</hotlnk>). If the retainer, from Step 3, is round, there will also
                be a thrust washer behind the auxiliary drive gear to remove.
            </para>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
